From: ms178 / Clear Linux (rebased by Arena Agent for glibc 2.43)
Date: 2026-06-04
Subject: [PATCH] Clear Linux libm hot-path optimisations + IFUNC dispatchers

This is the rebased and bug-fixed version of clear.patch:

  * Folded the SECTION/cold-path refactor of e_cosh.c (dbl-64) from
    Adhemerval Zanella's libm rework series.
  * Added the cosh-fma IFUNC dispatcher in sysdeps/x86_64/fpu/multiarch.
  * **Fixed: versioned_symbol GLIBC_2_44 -> GLIBC_2_43.**  The original
    patch referenced a symbol version that does not exist in 2.43;
    it was dead-stripped on the v3 build (MINIMUM_X86_ISA_LEVEL=3
    excludes the whole IFUNC block) but broke the moment you built
    without _optimize_v3.  Now matches what e_coshf.c (already
    upstream) does at GLIBC_2_43.
  * Folded the asinh-fma IFUNC dispatcher with SECTION/asinh-fma
    plumbing.
  * Folded the memmove-unaligned 64-byte ENTRY_P2ALIGN(...,6) tweak
    (avoids ~15% perf regression on sub-vector-size memmove on Intel).
  * Folded the four libm Makefile entries that pin
    -mprefer-vector-width and -fno-tree-vectorize for sin/cos/exp/exp2.

Rebased to upstream 18b97b03b7442d8ba0860e43145f8724c9e77b17 with -U10
context (zero fuzz, exact line numbers).  All 4 new files are now
included as proper add-file hunks.

